From @@mcgurn@gh@n @end|ng |rom dundee@@c@uk  Mon Feb  2 15:47:48 2015
From: @@mcgurn@gh@n @end|ng |rom dundee@@c@uk (Stuart McGurnaghan (Staff))
Date: Mon, 2 Feb 2015 14:47:48 +0000
Subject: [R-jobs] Software Developer Position
Message-ID: <DBXPR04MB318527BDD8891547DD70B79C13C0@DBXPR04MB318.eurprd04.prod.outlook.com>

Where:                       University of Dundee, Scotland UK

Salary range:           Grade 7 (?30,434 - ?32,277) REF: MDN0953

Duration of Post:    One year in the first instance

College:                      Medicine, Dentistry and Nursing
School:                       Medicine
Division:                     Population Health Sciences

Location:               Medical Research Institute, Ninewells Hospital & Medical School Campus, University of Dundee, DD1 9SY.

Closing Date:          3 March 2015


We are seeking a person with good programming skills to provide a key link between the source of our raw data and the analytics team. Our data can come from many different sources in different formats and has often had minimal cleaning or processing before we receive it. The data providers often provide flat files which are processed in Python and translated to database format. Our analytics team comprises machine learning specialists, biostatisticians and epidemiologists. The key responsibilities of the post are to liaise with those providing the data to help them provide it in an appropriate format and to assist in the warehousing of the data including processing and documenting the data to make it ready for the analytics team. Essential attributes are good interpersonal skills and an ability to communicate clearly, experience with a relational database management package such as MySQL and familiarity with the Linux environment. Good working knowledge in any of C/C++, Python or Java. Experience with an array programming language such as R or Matlab would be useful though not essential.

